									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2648492)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2648492">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1474466537 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Sep 2016 14:02</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2648492">
									

<p>The plot is hilarious and I honestly didn't see the end coming, but the prose is jarring. It's so chock-full of direct characterization and direct exposition that I felt like I was reading someone's playthrough of a survival-horror game (the events are very video game-y too - finding pistols in the hands of dead bodies, finding convenient trucks with supplies, the completely linear plotline, etc.), which screwed with my sense of immersion pretty severely. No-vote.</p>

							</div>

								
					
