		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2661786)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2661786">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kalinin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2203795); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2203795&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205810" alt="Kalinin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2203795)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kalinin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2203795); return false;" >Kalinin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1475006110 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Sep 2016 19:55</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2661786">
									

<p>I wondered briefly if I was reading &quot;Containment Breach: The Tale<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-294797-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-294797-1')">1</a></sup>&quot;, which would have annoyed the hell out of me, but it turned out to more closely resemble &quot;The Martian,&quot; a juxtaposition I found pretty hilarious. I actually enjoyed the self-aware, goofy narrator in this context, which is not something I usually go for, probably because he matched the sort of inherently ridiculous, but strangely consistent-with-Foundationverse-logic premise. And the line at the end, given the rest of the story, felt earned enough that I didn't roll my eyes. Pretty decent, overall.</p>
<p>My only quibble is that this feels more like the intro to something than it does an entirely self-contained tale. So if you want to do future installments, hey, there you go.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-294797-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-294797-1')">1</a>. That's not meant to be as dismissive as it surely sounds</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
					
